Prerequisites
Before running Bezaleel, make sure you have the following:

1. Hardware Requirements
Recommended: 16 GB RAM or more (32 GB ideal for better AI performance)
Working microphone
Internet connection (for voice recognition, opening websites, and initial model download) 

2. Software Requirements
Python 3.9 or higher
JupyterLab (recommended) or Jupyter Notebook
Ollama (for local AI) → Download from https://ollama.com
FFmpeg (required for louder voice output)

3. Ollama Model
Pull the Gemma model (light and fast):

ollama pull gemma2:2b
Keep ollama serve running in the background (Command Prompt / Terminal).

4. Python Packages
Create a requirements.txt file with the following content:

gtts
speechrecognition
pyaudio
pydub
ipywidgets
ollama
pandas
numpy
openpyxl
Install all dependencies with:
pip install -r requirements.txt

5. Optional
OpenWeatherMap API key (if you want to enable weather feature) from https://home.openweathermap.org/api_keys 
to get API key
